parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear glass window adhesive can cause the window to fall out of the convertible top, creating a safety hazard for the driver, passengers, and pedestrians.
symptoms: The rear glass window becomes detached from the convertible top
causing a potential hazard while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Convertible Top Rear Window Adhesive Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the adhesive holding the rear window to the convertible top can cause the window to detach while driving, potentially striking other vehicles or pedestrians, and posing a significant safety risk.
symptoms: The rear window becomes loose or falls out of the convertible top
and may cause damage to the vehicle or other objects.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Window Separation from Convertible Top
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The separation of the rear window from the convertible top can cause the window to fall off while driving, potentially causing accidents or injuries to occupants or other road users.
symptoms: The rear window becomes detached from the convertible top
water enters the vehicle through the rear window
the rear window falls off while driving
the rear window becomes loose or separates from the top at the corner.
